      <h1>Base64 vs URL Encoding: What's the Difference?</h1>

      <p>Base64 encoding and URL encoding (percent-encoding) are two fundamentally different encoding schemes that developers frequently encounter. Despite both being called "encoding," they serve different purposes, produce different outputs, and are used in different contexts. Understanding when to use each prevents data corruption, security issues, and interoperability bugs.</p>

